<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,1871,1929]" lastBlockId="9.[192,1440,221,572]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clemens" authorityYear="1860" box="[232,338,1871,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,338,1871,1895]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Amorbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Phillips-Rodriguez, E. &amp; J. A. Powell" box="[524,974,1872,1896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" refId="ref8636" refString="Phillips-Rodriguez, E., and J. A. Powell. 2007. Phylogenetic relationships, systematics, and biology of the species of Amorbia Clemens (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae: Sparganothini). Zootaxa 1670, 109 p." type="book" year="2007">Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, who included 29 species in their treatment. They presented host records for 11 of the species, and in cases where one than one rearing was involved, polyphagy seems to be the norm, with a total of 27 plant families documented as hosts for one or more species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clemens" authorityYear="1860" box="[418,524,253,277]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[418,524,253,277]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The continued efforts of 
<bibRefCitation author="Janzen, D. H. &amp; W. Hallwachs" box="[839,1202,254,278]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8505" refString="Janzen, D. H., and W. Hallwachs. 2009. Dynamic database for an inventory of the macrocaterpillar fauna, and its food plants and parasitoids, of Area de Conservacion Guanacaste (ACG), northwestern Costa Rica (nn-SRNP-nnnnn voucher codes). Available at http: // janzen. sas. upenn. edu. (Last accessed Dec 12 2018.)" type="url" year="2009">Janzen and Hallwachs (2009)</bibRefCitation>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1242,1374,254,278]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
have added many new hosts but revealed no conspicuous patterns other than polyphagy. During the study in 
<collectingCountry box="[224,329,319,343]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, two species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clemens" authorityYear="1860" box="[515,621,319,343]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[515,621,319,343]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,221,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authority="Phillips and Powell, 2007" authorityName="Phillips and Powell" authorityYear="2007" box="[232,723,351,376]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cacao">
<emphasis box="[232,410,351,375]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia cacao</emphasis>
Phillips and Powell, 2007
</taxonomicName>
, described from specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1110,1240,352,376]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1296,1435,352,376]" name="Guatemala" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, was reported from Yanayacu by 
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski, J. &amp; J. Wojtusiak" box="[593,986,384,409]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="585 - 603" refId="ref8894" refString="Razowski, J., and J. Wojtusiak. 2010. Some Tortricidae from the East Cordillera in Ecuador reared from larvae in Yanayacu Biological Station in Ecuador (Insecta: Lepidoptera). Genus 21: 585 - 603." type="journal article" year="2010">Razowski and Wojtusiak (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1033,1168,384,409]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, this species has been reared from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.M.C.Dumeril" authorityYear="1805" box="[340,477,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.Lindley" authorityYear="1830" box="[486,620,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Clusiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Clusiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley &amp; John" authorityYear="1830" box="[630,747,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Candolle &amp; Candolle" authorityYear="1824" box="[758,940,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Flacourtiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Flacourtiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Candolle &amp; Perleb" authorityYear="1818" box="[950,1119,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Juglandaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1129,1259,418,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lauraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1269,1384,418,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[192,759,450,474]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sabiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sabiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Sabiaceae (
<bibRefCitation author="Phillips-Rodriguez, E. &amp; J. A. Powell" box="[325,751,450,474]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8636" refString="Phillips-Rodriguez, E., and J. A. Powell. 2007. Phylogenetic relationships, systematics, and biology of the species of Amorbia Clemens (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae: Sparganothini). Zootaxa 1670, 109 p." type="book" year="2007">Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[799,899,450,474]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
it was reared once from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1184,1261,449,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1184,1261,449,473]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Rubus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName box="[1313,1428,450,474]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,221,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authority="Phillips and Powell, 2007" authorityName="Phillips and Powell" authorityYear="2007" box="[232,775,482,507]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colubrana">
<emphasis box="[232,466,482,506]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia colubrana</emphasis>
Phillips and Powell, 2007
</taxonomicName>
was reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1005,1123,482,506]" name="Colombia" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1238,482,506]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1299,1360,483,506]" name="Peru" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Peru</collectingCountry>
, above about 
<quantity box="[269,359,515,539]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
elevation (
<bibRefCitation author="Phillips-Rodriguez, E. &amp; J. A. Powell" box="[494,936,515,539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8636" refString="Phillips-Rodriguez, E., and J. A. Powell. 2007. Phylogenetic relationships, systematics, and biology of the species of Amorbia Clemens (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae: Sparganothini). Zootaxa 1670, 109 p." type="book" year="2007">Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell 2007</bibRefCitation>
). No larval hosts were previously known. In 
<collectingCountry box="[226,328,548,572]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
it was reared once from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1821" box="[631,693,547,571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[631,693,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Pilea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[751,887,548,572]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Urticaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
